FBIS4-33440 "drlat109bb_94003" FBIS-LAT-94-109 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 INTER-AMERICAN AFFAIRS Brazil's Franco Meets, Backs Haiti's Aristide Brazil's Franco Meets, Backs Haiti's Aristide PY0706003394 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 2200 GMT 6 Jun 94 PY0706003394 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network Portuguese BFN [Report by Luiz Augusto Mendonca in Belem, Para State] [Excerpts] Today, here, President Itamar Franco opened the 24th OAS General Assembly. He advocated strengthening the OAS as a political and diplomatic forum dedicated to finding peaceful, negotiated settlements to the issues affecting the 34 OAS member countries. [passage omitted] This afternoon, Franco held a private meeting with ousted Haitian President Jean-Bertrand Aristide, who came to Belem to ask the Brazilian Government to support his reinstatement as Haitian president. Franco reaffirmed his support for Aristide, and once again condemned all totalitarian regimes. Later tonight, Franco will host a dinner at the Para State Assembly club for the foreign delegates who are attending the OAS meeting.
